text: Daphnella proxima is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Raphitomidae.Worldwide Mollusc Species Data Base: Daphnella proxima ==Description== The length of this shell attains 38 mm. The shell is a long spiral. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs in the East China Sea. They have been found along the Japanese coast in places like Okinawa. ==References== * Oyama, K., Y. Takemura et al. 1958 The molluscan shells. Tokyo 1: 61 ==External links== * proxima Category:Gastropods described in 1958
title: Daphnella proxima
